title:
['Shiva Kovil (no 4) of Polonnaruwa Kingdom – ශිව දේවාලය (අංක 4)']

Rating:
['1', '2.00']

Content:

Lord Siva
Of the three gods of the Hindu trinity – Brahma the Creator, Vishnu the Preserver, and Siva the Destroyer and Restorer – Siva was especially popular and widely worshiped in southern India.
This kovil, identified as Siva Kovil No 4 on the ancient city of  Polonnaruwa is in ruins and belongs to the Chola era (1017-1070)
 





